#Windows Backup Procedure
## Purpose
This document explains the backup procedures used to back up Windows and ensure recovery in case of failure.

## Types of Backups

### 1. Full Backup
Copies all files and folders.

### 2. Incremental Backup
Backs up only changed files since the last backup.

### 3. Differential Backup
Backs up all changes since the last full backup.

---

## Backup Schedule

| Backup Type | Frequency |
|---|---|
| Full Backup | Weekly |
| Incremental Backup | Daily |

---

## Backup Storage

- External HDD
- Cloud storage
- Network storage

---

#Backup Windows procedure
1. Open Backup Settings
2. Connect backup drive
3. Select folders
4. Run backup
5. Verify successful completion

---
## Verification Steps

After backup:
- Confirm files exist
- Test file restoration
- Check backup logs

---

## Common Issues

### Backup Fails
Possible causes:
- Low disk space
- Drive disconnected
- Permission issues

---

### Slow Backup Speed
Possible causes:
- Large file sizes
- Network congestion
- Faulty drive

---

## Recovery Procedure

1. Open backup utility
2. Select restore point
3. Choose files/folders
4. Restore to destination
5. Verify restored files

---

## Best Practices

- Keep multiple backup copies
- Test backups regularly
- Store one backup offsite
- Encrypt sensitive backups
- Monitor backup logs

